In the Cantera C++ User's Manual it states: 

"Simply open the workspace `cantera.dsw' in folder `win32', set the 
Active
Configuration on the Build menu to examples - Win32 Release, and 
build the project. This will build the
Cantera kernel static libraries and a test program examples.exe. 
Execute `examples.exe' to verify that Cantera has
been correctly installed."

There is no 'examples' in the Build menu->Active Configuration.  How 
do I get the examples in Visual Studio?  I've already built 'all' and 
there were no errors.
